comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
The prototype of the NA-64, one of 230 for France, with 200 ordered by the air force and 30 by the navy. 119 of the aircraft ordered were delivered to Canada when France fell during deliveries. This is the only aircraft type legitimately known as the Yale and this individual aircraft was kept back in Inglewood for use in creating the necessary manuals. It was the last to arrive in Canada and served throughout the war as RCAF # 3464.

Doug MacPhail
